OL,3,CLegendary West Indies cricketer Sir
OL,4,CGarfield Sobers dies aged 89
OL,6,FSir Garfield Sobers, the "greatest
OL,7,Fcricketer the world has ever seen,"
OL,8,Fhas died aged 89.
OL,10,FBorn in Barbados, Garfield St Aubrun
OL,11,FSobers played for the West Indies, and
OL,12,Fwas known to be one of the best
OL,13,Fcricketers in history.
OL,15,FHe had 93 Test appearances, with his
OL,16,Ffirst and last against England, and
OL,17,Fscored a total of 8,032 runs at an
OL,18,Faverage of 57.78, while his 235
OL,19,Fwickets came at a cost of 34.03.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/6
