OL,3,CLegendary West Indies cricketer Sir
OL,4,CGarfield Sobers dies aged 89
OL,6,FHe died just 11 days short of his 90th
OL,7,Fbirthday.
OL,9,FKishore Shallow, president of Cricket
OL,10,FWest Indies, paid tribute to who he
OL,11,Fcalled the "greatest cricketer the
OL,12,Fworld has ever seen" and said Sobers'
OL,13,Flegacy would live on.
OL,15,F"His mastery of batting, bowling and
OL,16,Ffielding was unparalleled, but his
OL,17,Ftrue significance reached far beyond
OL,18,Fthe boundary ropes," he said, adding
OL,19,Fthat his "brilliance carried the name
OL,20,Fof the West Indies with distinction
OL,21,Facross the world".
