OL,3,CLegendary West Indies cricketer Sir
OL,4,CGarfield Sobers dies aged 89
OL,6,FHe registered his first Test century
OL,7,Faged 23 in 1958, when he achieved a
OL,8,Fworld record of 365 not out against
OL,9,FPakistan.
OL,11,FFrom 1968 to 1974, Sobers spent six
OL,12,Fseasons in England playing for
OL,13,FNottinghamshire, where he hit six
OL,14,Fsuccessive sixes in a single over from
OL,15,FGlamorgan's Malcolm Nash.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/6
