OL,3,CLegendary West Indies cricketer Sir
OL,4,CGarfield Sobers dies aged 89
OL,6,FNottinghamshire said they were
OL,7,F"extremely saddened" to hear about his
OL,8,Fdeath, and described Sobers as
OL,9,F"cricket's greatest-ever all-rounder,
OL,10,Fand an iconic figure in
OL,11,FNottinghamshire history."
OL,13,FIn 1975 he received a knighthood from
OL,14,Fthe late Queen Elizabeth II in
OL,15,FBridgetown Barbados.
OL,17,FEngland Cricket posted on X: "One of
OL,18,Fthe greatest to ever play the game.
OL,19,FForever in our hearts, Sir Garfield
OL,20,FSobers."
